{"id": 4566, "title": "Ticket #4566: Condor_rm of DAGMan doesn't work right on Windows", "description": "<blockquote>\nBillT just found this as a result of trying to fix a DAGMan test that fails on Windows...\n\n<p>Anyhow, if you condor_rm DAGMan on Windows, the DAGMan process just gets killed, so you don't get a rescue DAG, you don't kill node jobs, etc.\n\n</p><p>TJ says that on Windows we send a WM_CLOSE message to a daemoncore process before killing it -- if it responds to that, we don't hard kill it right away.  So the solution may be for DAGMan to become a GUI app on Windows (see the keyboardd for an example of this).</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4661\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4661'); return false;\" title=\"Document that condor_rm of DAGMan doesn't work right on Windows\">#4661</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nDocument that condor_rm of DAGMan doesn't work right on Windows</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2014-Sep-03 14:53</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/512838a298ed989d26239bac92ab602aa47608c4\">[41083]</a></span>: edit 8.2.3 known bug version history item <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=4566\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('4566'); return false;